21/03/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- On Thursday (20 March), federal President Svetozar Marovic announced a series of changes in the national army, intended in part to remove individuals who might obstruct war crimes co-operation.
He described the personnel changes as part of the general framework of democratic reforms.
Meanwhile, the Supreme Defence Council decided Thursday to relieve Maj Gen Aca Tomic of his duties as the head of the army's security office.
(BKTV, Vijesti, B92, Tanjug - 20/03/03)
